    "title": "Maharashtra Election Results 2024: Full List Of Winning Candidates",
    "text": "The Mahayuti won in 21 constituencies in the Mumbai region out of the total 36 seats, gaining power in India's financial capital.\nNDTV Profit Desk\n24 Nov 2024, 10:09 AM IST 24 Nov 2024, 09:46 AM IST 24 Nov 2024, 10:09 AM IST WhatsApp X (was Twitter) Facebook Telegram Save\nThe Mahayuti won 21 constituencies in the Mumbai region out of the total 36 seats, gaining power in India's financial capital. (Image Source: @BJP4India/X) The ruling Mahayuti, or NDA coalition, consisting of the Nationalist Congress Party, Shiv Sena, and Bharatiya Janata Party, won by a landslide margin in the 2024 Maharashtra assembly election results declared on Saturday. The alliance won 235 of the 288 seats.\nThe opposition Congress's Maha Vikas Aghadi, Shard Pawar's NCP, and Uddhav Thackeray's Shiv Sena lost more than anticipated by only securing 47 seats.\nThe final count showed that the BJP had won 132, the Shiv Sena 57, the NCP 41, the Congress 16, the Shiv Sena (UBT) 20, and the NCP (SP) 10 out of 288 Maharashtra assembly seats.\nThe Mahayuti won in 21 constituencies in the Mumbai region out of the total 36 seats, gaining power in India's financial capital. In Mumbai City district's 10 assembly seats, the Shiv Sena (UBT) and the BJP secured four wins each. The Congress managed to win two.\nAaditya Thackeray won the high-profile Worli assembly constituency with a margin of 8,801 votes over closest rival Milind Deora of the Shinde Sena.\nReal estate tycoon Mangal Prabhat Lodha of the BJP retained the upscale Malabar Hill constituency with a 68,019 margin.\nMumbai City Constituency-Wise Winners' List ALSO READ List Of Candidates With Highest And Lowest Victory Margins — Maharashtra Election Results 2024 Opinion List Of Candidates With Highest And Lowest Victory Margins — Maharashtra Election Results 2024 Read More Full List Of Winning Candidates The 288-member Assembly was approved by the state on November 20. There were 4,136 contestants in the race. The Mahayuti has won 235 of the 288 seats, according to the Election Commission.\nALSO READ Markets Could See Short Rally With NDA's Maharashtra Win, Says Motilal Oswal Opinion Markets Could See Short Rally With NDA's Maharashtra Win, Says Motilal Oswal Read More",
